festival.introText:
10 Years of Mint Festival! 

 

Happening earlier in the year to catch some summer rays, it returns to the beautifully sprawling Newsam Green Farm with four specifically designed stages, an all-new drum & bass offering and world-beating headliners.

reviews.body: Overpriced event with expensive drinks and an average lineup. Atmosphere was great. More (recycling) bins needed. 10/10 cheesy chips.

reviews.title: Review of Mint Festival
reviews.body: great music, great people, but seriously needs to sort out the shuttle bus system, standing in some sectioned off railings not knowing when you're leaving, sitting there for at least an hour to see half filled busses leaving and then finally giving up even though you've paid in advance for a shuttle bus ticket and walk to the other end of the venue to order an Uber for about 50 quid.  other then that the event was great. please sort it out for next year.

faqs.question: When is Mint Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Mint Festival returns to Newsam Green, Leeds on Saturday 23rd September 2023

faqs.question: How much are Mint Festival tickets?
faqs.answer: Tickets are currently on sale from £45+bf

faqs.question: How do you get to Mint Festival?
faqs.answer: There are no trains to Mint Festival. You can get a shuttle bus from Leeds city centre or taxi.

faqs.question: I am a customer with access requirements / I am disabled, how do I buy a ticket for Mint Festival 2022?
faqs.answer: You can buy tickets on this website.

faqs.question: Where is Mint Festival?
faqs.answer: Mint Festival is located at Newsam Green Farm in Leeds around 6 miles from Leeds city centre. It takes about 20 minutes from the city centre by bus or car. The postcode is LS15 9AD.

faqs.question: Are payment plan tickets available?
faqs.answer: Payment plan tickets are currently not on sale.

faqs.question: If Mint Festival tickets completely sell out, is there an allocation reserved for customers with access requirements and/or disabled customers?
faqs.answer: Mint Festival does not reserve an allocation of tickets for accessible customers. Once tickets are sold out, they are sold out.

faqs.question: How do I get to Mint Festival?
faqs.answer:
By Car - The quickest route from Leeds city centre is via the A63.

By Shuttle - Shuttle buses normally run on the days of the event, these will take you from Leeds City Centre to the festival site. Pick-up locations and running times are yet to be announced.

By Bus - The 167, 168 and 175 take you to the closest bus stops to the festival site.

 

By Rail - There are regular trains from Leeds city centre to Newsham Green via NORTHERN trains.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately, we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: I require a Personal Assistant in order to attend the event, must I buy a ticket for my PA?
faqs.answer: If you qualify for a PA to attend the event with you, you should buy a ticket for yourself and complete the access requirement form. You do not need to buy a ticket for the personal assistant, however if you do not qualify for a PA and tickets have sold out you will not be able to buy an additional ticket.

faqs.question: What happens If I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer:
Unfortunately, we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent.

 

Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: What disabled access facilities are available at Mint Festival?
faqs.answer:
We offer accessible car parking, personal assistant tickets and disabled toilets.

I am unsure if I qualify for the access facilities on offer

Automatic qualification applies to those able to supply the following

- documentation dated within the past 12 months or with valid date covering

The Event:

- Front page of DLA letter with PIP letter
- Front page of Attendance Allowance letter
- Blue badge accompanied by driver’s license photo card and/or
- passport photo page
- Evidence of being registered as severely sight impaired (blind)
- Recognised Assistance Dog ID card
- I am unable to provide any of the above

We recognise that the evidence above is not definitive. If you do not have any of the above evidence but wish to apply for particular access facilities you will need to complete the application form and provide a statement and supporting evidence. These applications will be considered on a case by case basis.

 

 

PLEASE EMAIL FOR AN ACCESS REQUIREMENT FORM stuart@themintclub.com

faqs.question: Does Mint Festival have any age restrictions?
faqs.answer: Yes you must be 18 or over to attend Mint Festival. You may be asked to show photo ID.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own food and drink into Mint Festival?
faqs.answer: You are not allowed to bring your own food and drink into Mint Festival. There will be a wide variety of food and drink stalls inside the festival, serving up organic, vegetarian and vegan options.
